It‚Äôs been interesting reversing my creative process: first working on the computer and then going to capture. Does this count as getting it in camera? Back in NY after a week in LA attending #AdobeMax. My mind is swimming with all the inspiration and information gleaned. Some days ideas seem to hide and I feel like I‚Äôm wandering through a desert, flipping over rocks and peering into crevices. In those moments I am grateful to be surrounded by so many talented friends. They motivate and inspire me, and remind me that the well never really runs dry.

While I was in LA I got to spend a lot of time with one of my closest and most talented friends, @veromeros. On my last day we ran outside for a 10 minute photoshoot before saying goodbye, and I made this collage for her. Love is an excellent prompt. What do you look to when you can‚Äôt find the answer within?

Swipe right to see the deconstruction. #adobepartner

I‚Äôm in LA for #AdobeMax! Yesterday they announced a bunch of new tools, including Aero which I have been beta testing for the last year.
I remember the first time I used Photoshop, and how much it changed the way I thought about photography. Then I fell in love with After Effects and it changed the way I understood video. These new tools are changing the way I think about my work in the world and how people can experience it.
Swipe through to see my process for making this AR collage. I used Photoshop, Dimension, Aero and Premiere Rush - all available in the App Store now.  #adobepartner

For the past few weeks I‚Äôve been working with an incredible team to bring a new experience to @lifeisbeautiful. In partnership with @sierraclub, our aim was to create an immersive audio/visual meditation space, inspired by the earth‚Äôs healing resonances and the Japanese practice of Shinrin-Yoku. While a motel in downtown Vegas might not be the most obvious space to reconnect with nature, it was truly moving to see attendees take a break from the loud, high energy festival and seek peace and calm within the Bath. Let it serve as a reminder that in this pivotal time the earth continues to offer us spaces of healing, but it is up to us to protect the future of our planet and humankind.
